[[Image:George-Shapiro-Friedman.jpg|thumb|right|George Shapiro, left, in 2006]] '''George Shapiro''' (born May 18, 1931) is an [[United States|American]] [[talent manager]] and [[television producer]]. He is among the most successful managers in [[show business]], best known for representing [[Jerry Seinfeld]], [[Carl Reiner]] and [[Andy Kaufman]], and served as a producer for the highly successful sitcom ''[[Seinfeld]]''.<ref name="variety">{{cite news |last1=Whetsell |first1=Tripp |title=Veteran Talent Manager George Shapiro Looks Back on Early Career |url=https://variety.com/2018/vintage/features/talent-manager-george-shapiro-1202819107/ |accessdate=September 24, 2018 |work=Variety |date=May 25, 2018}}</ref>
==Early life and education== Shapiro was born and raised in [[the Bronx]],<ref>New York, New York, Birth Index, 1910-1965</ref><ref name="jewsweek">{{cite news |last1=Cohen |first1=Benyamin |title=Last Comic Standing |url=http://contactben.com/thebronxboys/jewsweek/jews_week.html |accessdate=September 24, 2018 |work=Jewsweek |date=July 24, 2003}}</ref> where he met future business partner [[Howard West]] (1931–2015) in the third grade. He attended P.S. 80, [[DeWitt Clinton High School]] and [[New York University]].<ref name="time">{{cite news |last1=Isenberg |first1=Barbara |title=Meet the Bronx Boys |url=http://content.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,699415,00.html |accessdate=September 24, 2018 |work=Time |date=September 20, 2004}}</ref> He grew up in a Jewish family. When Shapiro was 12, [[Carl Reiner]] married Shapiro's aunt and became his uncle.<ref>Marc Maron, "Carl Reiner" episode of WTF podcast, 20130207</ref><ref name="variety" />
==Career== After graduating from NYU, Shapiro went to work in the mailroom at the [[William Morris Agency]] in [[New York City|New York]]. He advanced within the company and soon became an agent. One of his first assignments was to accompany [[Elvis Presley]] during his appearances on ''[[The Ed Sullivan Show]]''. Eventually, he began packaging programs including the hits ''[[The Steve Allen Show]]'', ''[[That Girl]]'' starring [[Marlo Thomas]], and ''[[Gomer Pyle]]'' starring [[Jim Nabors]]. He also packaged a number of specials for [[Dick Van Dyke]], [[Mary Tyler Moore]] and [[Carol Channing]].<ref name="variety"/><ref name="jewsweek"/>
Shapiro left William Morris to become a [[personal manager]] and producer along with his partner and friend, Howard West. They formed Shapiro/West Productions and executive produced the [[Emmy]], [[Peabody Award|Peabody]], and [[Golden Globe]] award-winning series, ''[[Seinfeld]]''. Shapiro was Andy Kaufman's personal manager for many years, executive producing the performer's special for [[Showtime (TV network)|Showtime]], ''Andy Kaufman at [[Carnegie Hall]]'', and one for [[American Broadcasting Company|ABC]], ''[[The Andy Kaufman Show]]''. He was executive producer with West on the 1999 [[Universal Pictures|Universal]] [[Biographical film|biopic]] ''[[Man on the Moon (film)|Man on the Moon]]'' starring [[Jim Carrey]] in the role of Andy Kaufman and [[Danny DeVito]] as Shapiro, and had a cameo in the movie as Mr. Besserman. He played a prominent role in the documentary ''[[Comedian (film)|Comedian]]''.<ref name="variety"/><ref name="jewsweek"/>
On June 30, 2012, people from the world of comedy gathered at the [[Beverly Wilshire Hotel]] in Beverly Hills to honor Shapiro. The [[David Lynch Foundation]] presented him with the first Lifetime of Bliss Award. He said he had been practicing [[Transcendental Meditation technique|Transcendental Meditation]] for 28 years.<ref>[http://dlf.tv/2013/highlights-of-david-lynch-foundations-night-of-comedy-honoring-george-shapiro/comment-page-1/#comment-1523 Highlights of David Lynch Foundation's Night of Comedy Honoring George Shapiro]</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=Jay Leno and Jerry Seinfeld on Transcendental Meditation|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=C4ttAprgRwQ|website=YouTube|accessdate=19 September 2015|date=22 July 2014|quote=TM, which I've been doing for, I think, it's 28 years ... Andy Kaufman introduced me to it and it's become a great experience for me.}}</ref>
